name: 04.Model Training and score
content:
Model Training and Validation

Model Used:

  • Gradient Boosting Classifier – selected for its ability to handle non-linear relationships, strong predictive power, and robustness with tabular data.

Features Used:

  • Internal_Audit_Score, External_Audit_Score, Fin_Score, Loss_Score, Past_Result, Location_Score.

Feature Importance:

  • Gradient Boosting provides feature importance rankings:
  • Internal_Audit_Score and External_Audit_Score – strong indicators of compliance risk.
  • Fin_Score – critical for identifying financially weak sites.
  • Loss_Score – directly tied to historical financial impact.
  • Past_Result – reflects reliability of the site over time.

Model Metrics:

  • Accuracy – Proportion of correct predictions.
  • Precision – Accuracy of high-risk predictions.
  • Recall (Sensitivity) – Ability to identify risky BTS sites.
  • F1 Score – Balance of precision and recall.
  • ROC-AUC – Discriminative ability between safe vs. risky sites.

Validation Strategy:

  • Split testing dataset for evaluation.
  • Cross-validation for robustness.
  • Confusion matrix to assess false positives/negatives (misclassifying a risky site as safe is most costly).
